  "text": "One of the distinguishing characteristics of Arabic script is the presence of a zigzag-shaped mark ‫,)ﺀ(‬ called Hamza, with some Arabic characters. The aim of using this metric is to expose the sensitivity of Arabic OCR systems to zigzag-shaped characters. [CITATION_1] compute the zigzag-shaped character accuracy by using equation (1). [CITATION_2] , an obstacle for Arabic OCR is recognising Arabic characters that contain a loop shape. To assess the effectiveness of Arabic OCR systems for recognising these characters, the accuracy of loop-shaped characters is also computed by equation (1).",
